5000|$|On 5 July, Interior Minister Mohammed Al-Ghabban resigned, {{which was}} accepted. The Interior {{ministry}} {{is responsible for}} police but not other forces providing security in Baghdad. In his resignation, al-Ghabban said that the security system was [...] "fundamentally flawed" [...] and called for changes to increase the ministry's power. Lieutenant General Abdulamir al-Shimmari, head of the Baghdad Operations Command of the Iraqi Army, along {{with the head of}} the division responsible for intelligence on Baghdad at the Ministry of the Interior and the official responsible for Baghdad in <b>the</b> <b>national</b> <b>security</b> <b>adviser's</b> office were removed from their posts by al-Abadi. Five convicts were executed and 40 suspected jihadists were arrested following the attack.|$|R
